{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Adrian Beria Blog","author":"Adrian Beria"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"95c42d7f-6b9f-59f0-a050-2197ea1825ea","excerpt":"Introduction Routing is the capacity to show different pages to the user. That means the user can move between different parts of an…","html":"<h2>Introduction</h2>\n<p>Routing is the capacity to show different pages to the user. That means the user can move between different parts of an application by entering a URL or clicking on an element.</p>\n<p>As you may already know, by default, React comes without routing. And to enable it in our project, we need to add a library named react-router.</p>\n<h2>When to use</h2>\n<p>When we need to connect different pages between each other.</p>\n<h2>Installing dependencies</h2>\n<p>For an already created project:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">yarn add yarn add react-router-dom</code></pre></div>\n<h2>Project structure</h2>\n<p>We’re gonna do a ducks pattern here as it’s the recomended way of doing Redux</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>src</p>\n<ul>\n<li>api</li>\n<li>components</li>\n<li>\n<p>ducks</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>contacts</p>\n<ul>\n<li>index.js</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>pages</li>\n<li>store</li>\n<li>App.js</li>\n<li>index.js</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>How to use</h2>\n<p>We will show it applies to a Navbar since it’s the most common case.</p>\n<p>In App.js we <strong>import { BrowserRouter as Router, Route } from “react-router-dom”</strong>, where Router will be the container of our routing system, and Route will be the component in charge of saying which component to show at which link:</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/React-Personal-Blog-Gatsby/static/a5ad61df2830e6efabb4ee9fa8d4bb29/88cc0/react-router-1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 88.05970149253731%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"code\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/React-Personal-Blog-Gatsby/static/a5ad61df2830e6efabb4ee9fa8d4bb29/fb8a0/react-router-1.png\"\n        srcset=\"/React-Personal-Blog-Gatsby/static/a5ad61df2830e6efabb4ee9fa8d4bb29/1a291/react-router-1.png 148w,\n/React-Personal-Blog-Gatsby/static/a5ad61df2830e6efabb4ee9fa8d4bb29/2bc4a/react-router-1.png 295w,\n/React-Personal-Blog-Gatsby/static/a5ad61df2830e6efabb4ee9fa8d4bb29/fb8a0/react-router-1.png 590w,\n/React-Personal-Blog-Gatsby/static/a5ad61df2830e6efabb4ee9fa8d4bb29/526de/react-router-1.png 885w,\n/React-Personal-Blog-Gatsby/static/a5ad61df2830e6efabb4ee9fa8d4bb29/fa2eb/react-router-1.png 1180w,\n/React-Personal-Blog-Gatsby/static/a5ad61df2830e6efabb4ee9fa8d4bb29/88cc0/react-router-1.png 1206w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Where Router needs to have only one child instead of what was shown, so instead it will be like this:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>BrowserRouter<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Route path<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"/about\"</span> component<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>About<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Route path<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"/contact\"</span> component<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>Contact<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>BrowserRouter<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<p>The important part is this:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Route path<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"/\"</span> exact component<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>Home<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Where path is the url path we’re going to use for Home component, so when a user clicks the Link from react-router-dom and if it has assigned to the <strong>to</strong> prop, the same path url, then it will take the user to the desired path.</p>\n<p>So… how do we actually manage our links? Inside Navbar of course! So inside we will import Link from react-router-dom:</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/React-Personal-Blog-Gatsby/static/ee96e5a7dcd2e84cd93f453ab15f2d41/ca8a9/react-router-2.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 169.61538461538464%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"code\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/React-Personal-Blog-Gatsby/static/ee96e5a7dcd2e84cd93f453ab15f2d41/fb8a0/react-router-2.png\"\n        srcset=\"/React-Personal-Blog-Gatsby/static/ee96e5a7dcd2e84cd93f453ab15f2d41/1a291/react-router-2.png 148w,\n/React-Personal-Blog-Gatsby/static/ee96e5a7dcd2e84cd93f453ab15f2d41/2bc4a/react-router-2.png 295w,\n/React-Personal-Blog-Gatsby/static/ee96e5a7dcd2e84cd93f453ab15f2d41/fb8a0/react-router-2.png 590w,\n/React-Personal-Blog-Gatsby/static/ee96e5a7dcd2e84cd93f453ab15f2d41/526de/react-router-2.png 885w,\n/React-Personal-Blog-Gatsby/static/ee96e5a7dcd2e84cd93f453ab15f2d41/fa2eb/react-router-2.png 1180w,\n/React-Personal-Blog-Gatsby/static/ee96e5a7dcd2e84cd93f453ab15f2d41/ca8a9/react-router-2.png 1560w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>The one called NavLink is a styled component with a custom name, it’s actually the Link we were talking about. Notice the pattern it has:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>NavLink\n    key<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>link<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>name<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n    to<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>link<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>path<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n    active<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token function\">handleActiveClass</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>currentUrl<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> link<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>url<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>link<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>name<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>NavLink<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Where the important prop is the “to” which indicates the path url we’re going to use.</p>\n<h2>Redirects</h2>\n<p>Sometimes when you work for a company they have to handle multiple languages so the URL can’t look like “www.website.com/programacion” for the Portuguese version which should be “www.website.com/programacao”, this is where redirects come in handy. I usually have a redirects.js file with the following structure:</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/React-Personal-Blog-Gatsby/static/69c43f2d6ae5062f12fda229b622aac1/4e3b5/react-router-3.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 45.46632124352332%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"code\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/React-Personal-Blog-Gatsby/static/69c43f2d6ae5062f12fda229b622aac1/fb8a0/react-router-3.png\"\n        srcset=\"/React-Personal-Blog-Gatsby/static/69c43f2d6ae5062f12fda229b622aac1/1a291/react-router-3.png 148w,\n/React-Personal-Blog-Gatsby/static/69c43f2d6ae5062f12fda229b622aac1/2bc4a/react-router-3.png 295w,\n/React-Personal-Blog-Gatsby/static/69c43f2d6ae5062f12fda229b622aac1/fb8a0/react-router-3.png 590w,\n/React-Personal-Blog-Gatsby/static/69c43f2d6ae5062f12fda229b622aac1/526de/react-router-3.png 885w,\n/React-Personal-Blog-Gatsby/static/69c43f2d6ae5062f12fda229b622aac1/fa2eb/react-router-3.png 1180w,\n/React-Personal-Blog-Gatsby/static/69c43f2d6ae5062f12fda229b622aac1/4e3b5/react-router-3.png 1544w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>And we can just map them easily:</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/React-Personal-Blog-Gatsby/static/a7c396e94419662aaf7a2eda9866b456/5686e/react-router-4.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 93.61997226074897%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"code\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/React-Personal-Blog-Gatsby/static/a7c396e94419662aaf7a2eda9866b456/fb8a0/react-router-4.png\"\n        srcset=\"/React-Personal-Blog-Gatsby/static/a7c396e94419662aaf7a2eda9866b456/1a291/react-router-4.png 148w,\n/React-Personal-Blog-Gatsby/static/a7c396e94419662aaf7a2eda9866b456/2bc4a/react-router-4.png 295w,\n/React-Personal-Blog-Gatsby/static/a7c396e94419662aaf7a2eda9866b456/fb8a0/react-router-4.png 590w,\n/React-Personal-Blog-Gatsby/static/a7c396e94419662aaf7a2eda9866b456/526de/react-router-4.png 885w,\n/React-Personal-Blog-Gatsby/static/a7c396e94419662aaf7a2eda9866b456/fa2eb/react-router-4.png 1180w,\n/React-Personal-Blog-Gatsby/static/a7c396e94419662aaf7a2eda9866b456/5686e/react-router-4.png 1442w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Redirects are self explanatory, they require two props, <strong>from</strong> and <strong>to</strong>. As for how to handle different language, that’s a post for another day.</p>\n<h2>History</h2>\n<p>We can access the history of the URLs the user has visited.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> history <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">useHistory</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2>Nesting Routes</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Route path<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"parent\"</span> component<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>Parent<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">Parent</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Route path<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"child\"</span> component<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>Child<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Route path<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"other\"</span> component<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>Other<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2>Switch</h2>\n<p>When a <Switch> is rendered, it will only render the first child <Route> that matches the current location.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token comment\">// v4</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">App</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n  <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Switch<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Route exact path<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"/\"</span> component<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>Home<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Route path<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"/about\"</span> component<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>About<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Route path<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"/contact\"</span> component<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>Contact<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>Switch<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>Summary</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Import Router and Route inside App.js.</li>\n<li>Make Router your container and inside add all your routes, saying which path will be assigned to which component.</li>\n<li>Inside your Navbar, import Link and add it to your menus, so when they’re clicked they will take you to the component you want, the <strong>to</strong> prop needs to be the same as the Route.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\n<p>We check how to use React Router.</p>\n<p>See you on the next post.</p>\n<p>Sincerely,</p>\n<p><strong>Eng Adrian Beria.</strong></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"React Router","date":"March 29, 2020"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/11-react-router/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/12-react-modal/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"React Modal"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/13-react-table/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"React Table"}}}}